                  <handDesc>
                     <p>The first hand is of a strictly commercial character, practised but awkward. The second hand, of which only three letters survive at the buttom of the fragment, is clearly of a more distinguished type, with square letters carefully formed and spaced. Written along the fibers of the verso and close to its right edge (hence, the left edge of the recto) are the remains of a docket.</p>
